Name: Dr. Sarfaraz Ahmed Bhutto
Highest Education: Dr. Sarfaraz Ahmed Bhutto achieved the PhD degree in the field of Finance. Dr. Bhutto is currently working as Assistant Professor at Fast School of Management Sciences, National University of computer and emerging sciences, Karachi. Dr. Bhutto has a diverse teaching and research experience. Previously, he served in Shah Abdul Latif Univrsity, Khairpur, The Shaikh Ayaz University Shikarpur and Dadabhoy Institute of Higher Education Sukkur Campus as a Faculty. His research focuses on Financial digitalization, the Potential for persistent elevated inflation and higher interest rates, Asset bubbles and market fragility, Climate-related risk and finance, Digital assets (crypto assets, stable coins, and central bank digital currencies), Corporate solvency, and capital structure. The Journal of Financial Innovation, which is a SSCI and impact factor journal under the domain of finance, Dr. Bhutto is working for them as a full time reviewer. Dr. Bhutto has published several research papers in national and international journals on research interest mentioned above.
